## 1Ô∏è‚É£ PayPal Subscription Setup

### Create Your Subscription Plan

1. **Log into PayPal Business Account**
   - Go to: https://www.paypal.com/businessmanage/account/products
   - If you don't have a Business account, upgrade at paypal.com/business

2. **Create New Subscription Plan**
   - Click "Create subscription button"
   - Choose "Subscription" type

3. **Configure Plan Details**
   ```
   Plan Name: Powerboat Insider Monthly Newsletter
   Price: $9.99 USD
   Billing Cycle: Every 1 month
   Trial Period: None (or add 30-day trial if desired)
   ```

4. **Get Your Plan ID**
   - After creation, PayPal will provide a Plan ID
   - It looks like: `P-XXXXXXXXXXXXXXXXXXXX`
   - Copy this ID

5. **Update HTML Files**
   - Open `thank-you.html`
   - Find: `plan_id=YOUR_PLAN_ID`
   - Replace with your actual Plan ID
   - Do the same in `newsletter-sample.html`

### PayPal Button Customization (Alternative)

If you prefer a PayPal button instead of direct link:

1. Go to PayPal Button Creator
2. Select "Subscribe"
3. Configure your plan
4. Copy the generated HTML
5. Replace the subscribe links in your pages

---

## 2Ô∏è‚É£ Email Marketing Integration

### Recommended Services
- **Mailchimp** (Free up to 500 contacts)
- **ConvertKit** (Best for creators)
- **ActiveCampaign** (Advanced automation)

### Setup Process (Mailchimp Example)

1. **Create Mailchimp Account**
   - Sign up at mailchimp.com
   - Create a new audience

2. **Create Signup Form**
   - Go to Audience ‚Üí Signup forms
   - Create embedded form
   - Copy the form action URL

3. **Integrate with Landing Page**
   
   Replace the `handleSubmit` function in `index.html`:

   ```javascript
   function handleSubmit(event) {
       event.preventDefault();
       
       const firstName = document.getElementById('firstName').value;
       const email = document.getElementById('email').value;
       
       // Submit to Mailchimp
       fetch('YOUR_MAILCHIMP_FORM_ACTION_URL', {
           method: 'POST',
           headers: {
               'Content-Type': 'application/x-www-form-urlencoded',
           },
           body: `FNAME=${encodeURIComponent(firstName)}&EMAIL=${encodeURIComponent(email)}`
       })
       .then(() => {
           // Redirect to thank you page
           window.location.href = `thank-you.html?name=${encodeURIComponent(firstName)}`;
       })
       .catch(error => {
           console.error('Error:', error);
           alert('Something went wrong. Please try again.');
       });
   }
   ```

4. **Set Up Automation**
   - Create automated email with PDF attachment
   - Trigger: When someone subscribes to your audience
   - Content: Welcome email + download link

### Email Automation Sequence

**Email 1** (Immediate - Welcome)
- Subject: "Your FREE Powerboat Show Guide is Here! üö§"
- Include PDF as attachment
- Include download link backup
- Brief welcome message

**Email 2** (Day 3 - Value)
- Subject: "Did you know this about the Annapolis show?"
- Share 3 insider tips not in the guide
- Soft mention of newsletter

**Email 3** (Day 7 - Upsell)
- Subject: "Ready for monthly powerboat insights?"
- Highlight newsletter benefits
- Include sample newsletter link
- Strong CTA to subscribe

---

## 3Ô∏è‚É£ Create Your Lead Magnet PDF

### What to Include in "2025 Powerboat Show Guide"

**Page 1: Cover**
- Title: "The Complete 2025 US Powerboat Show Guide"
- Subtitle: "Everything You Need for an Amazing Experience"
- Date: October 2-5, 2025

**Page 2-3: Show Overview**
- Event dates and hours
- Ticket information and pricing
- Show layout map
- Preview day information

**Page 4-5: Parking & Transportation**
- Parking garage locations and costs
- Shuttle bus schedules
- Uber/Lyft pickup points
- Walking routes from hotels

**Page 6-7: Dining Recommendations**
- Breakfast spots near the show
- Lunch options within walking distance
- Dinner reservations (make them early!)
- Quick grab-and-go options

**Page 8-9: Show Navigation Strategy**
- Best times to visit (avoid peak crowds)
- Recommended viewing route
- Must-see exhibitors
- New boat launches to watch for

**Page 10-11: Boat Categories Guide**
- Center consoles
- Bowriders
- Cruisers
- Sport boats
- What to look for in each category

**Page 12: Insider Tips**
- Bring comfortable shoes
- Download show app
- Business card collection strategy
- Photo-taking etiquette
- Test ride signup process

### PDF Creation Tools
- **Canva** (easiest, templates available)
- **Adobe InDesign** (professional)
- **Google Docs** (free, export as PDF)
- **Microsoft Word** (export as PDF)

### Design Tips
- Use high-quality boat images
- Keep branding consistent with website
- Make it print-friendly (8.5" x 11")
- Include your logo and website on every page
- Add page numbers

